  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it breathe before cooking</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong>as finely as you can</p><p>Chop most of the <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks (save some for garnish!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>in a large bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>Hat Yai marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1629302713871-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
